    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"575698\">Bernd Losert</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/Reflective.20subcategories.20stable.20under.20pullback/near/421803454\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Just want to mention that if C is already a pullback involving D with F : C → D being one of the projections, then it all works out. I originally asked my question because I was hoping for a more general result or maybe a reference with some theorems.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I take this back. Actually, it does not work out they way I thought. Dang...</p>",
