    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"575698\">@Bernd Losert</span>  Even though I feel like you want something general, my intuition would be to assume at least a set of generators in your categories. The reason for this is that you want to construct a reflector, and in practice, this kind of functors is best described as a colimit of generators</p>",
        "id": 422289406,
        "sender_full_name": "Rémy Tuyéras",
        "timestamp": 1708367942
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Found something akin to what I want: <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/reflective+sub-%28infinity%2C1%29-category#cocartesian_fiber_over_a_reflective_subcategory\">https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/reflective+sub-%28infinity%2C1%29-category#cocartesian_fiber_over_a_reflective_subcategory</a></p>",
